        "title": "Add values to existing JTable dynamically",
        "body": "<p>I've created a JTable using following way. This table has 5 columns and 4 rows.\nAll 4 rows are empty in this status.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String[] columns = {\"Emplotee ID\",\"Name\",\"Address\",\"City\",\"Salary\"};\n\n//Table that already have 4 empty rows\nDefaultTableModel model = new DefaultTableModel(columns,4); \nJTable detail = new JTable(model);\nJScrollPane scroll = new JScrollPane(detail);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Now I want to add values into those empty rows using String array.\nThe GUI of this program has 5 JTextFields to get user input. When I enter values into JTextFileds and click Add button, all JTextFiled values get by String array named values.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>String[] values = new String[6];\n//When click addButton all textFiled data should go into table\naddButton.addMouseListener(new MouseAdapter(){ \n    @Override\n    public void mouseClicked(MouseEvent evt){\n        values[0] = idField.getText(); //get JTextFields data into array \n        values[1] = nameField.getText();\n        values[2] = addressField.getText();\n        values[3] = cityField.getText();\n        values[4] = salaryField.getText();\n\n        //What now?\n    }\n});\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I know I can use this to add new row into the table. But this is not the feature what I want.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>DefaultTableModel newModel = (DefaultTableModel)detail.getModel();\nnewModel.addRow(values);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
